graph.name: 127_pubchem_pathway_toc
pubchem_description: This classification was created automatically from the PubChem Pathway TOC on 2023/12/26.
Note that in some cases a number of highly populated nodes - those for which all or nearly all IDs have information - have been left out of the tree.
The sections, along with their child subsections, that are not shown in this tree are: Create Date, Modify Date, and Record Title.

nodes.name: Identity
nodes.description: Information describing the identity of this pathway, including the data source and external identifier.

nodes.name: Source
nodes.description: Data source from which this pathway record was derived.

nodes.name: External ID
nodes.description: The identifier used for this pathway by the external data source.

nodes.name: Creators
nodes.description: Creators of this pathway record in the original data source.

nodes.name: Pathway Information
nodes.description: General information about this pathway.

nodes.name: Taxonomic Scope
nodes.description: Indicates if the pathway is organism-specific or conserved.

nodes.name: Taxonomy
nodes.description: Source organism of this pathway.

nodes.name: Category
nodes.description: Descriptive category of this pathway (e.g., signaling, metabolic, disease).

nodes.name: Record Description
nodes.description: Textual summary about this pathway

nodes.name: Diagram
nodes.description: Schematic overview of this pathway.  Clicking this diagram directs to the corresponding pathway record in the data source.

nodes.name: Interactions
nodes.description: Specific interactions between biochemicals involved in this pathway.

nodes.name: Chemicals
nodes.description: Chemicals involved in this pathway.

nodes.name: Glycans
nodes.description: Glycans involved in this pathway.

nodes.name: Proteins
nodes.description: Proteins involved in this pathway.

nodes.name: GlycoProteins
nodes.description: Glycoproteins involved in this pathway.

nodes.name: Genes
nodes.description: Genes involved in this pathway.

nodes.name: GlycoGenes
nodes.description: Glycogenes involved in this pathway. Glycogene includes genes associated with glycan synthesis such as glycosyltransferase, sugar nucleotide synthases, sugar-nucleotide transporters, sulfotransferases, etc.

nodes.name: Related Pathways
nodes.description: Related pathway records in PubChem (e.g. linked pathways).

nodes.name: Linked Pathways
nodes.description: Linked pathways provided by original source. Available link types are conserved, linked, subset, and superset. "Conserved" means the linked pathway is conserved in evolution for the current one. "Linked" means the linked pathway and the current one are connected to each other in a larger network. "Superset" means the linked pathway contains the current one. "Subset" means linked pathway is contained within the current one.

nodes.name: GlycoPathways
nodes.description: Pathways that involve glycoproteins.

nodes.name: Literature
nodes.description: Scientific articles associated with this pathway, provided by the data source.

nodes.name: Consolidated References
nodes.description: The consolidated references include literature data from all sources including Reactome, WikiPathways, PharmGKB, PathBank, LIPID MAPS, etc.

nodes.name: Classification
nodes.description: Classifications and ontologies of this pathway.

nodes.name: NCI Thesaurus Tree
nodes.description: NCI Thesaurus (NCIt) hierarchy

nodes.name: Information Sources
nodes.description: Sources of annotation information attached to PubChem compounds
